HEADWORD: Ratiocinative
<hw>Ra`ti*oc"i*na*tive</hw>
<pr>(r⟦acr⟧sh`⟦icr⟧*⟦ocr⟧s"⟦icr⟧*n⟦asl⟧*t⟦icr⟧v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>ratiocinativus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Characterized by, or
addicted to, ratiocination; consisting in the comparison of propositions
or facts, and the deduction of inferences from the comparison;
argumentative; <as>as, a <ex>ratiocinative</ex> process</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>ratiocinative</qex> meditativeness of his character.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ratiocinatory</ent>⟦br⟧
